posts.name: Jackson
posts.cooked:
I am setting my TalonFX speed but it’s not changing.  When I run the code to make it run, I sometimes get this error:

Device firmware could not be retrieved. Check that the device is running v6 firmware, the device ID is correct, the specified CAN bus is correct, and the device is powered.

It might be that I’m not setting control to the right thing.  Currently it is on VelocityVoltage.  The function motor.set(speed), and I put a print statement right in front of it such that I know it’s calling the function, but it’s still not setting the speed.  Someone please help.

Try using CTRE ’s Tuner X to update the motor firmware.

posts.name: Mohammed
posts.cooked:
Ah, I see. Well here are multiple reasons this error could appear. Double-check if the firmware is up to date, ensure the wiring on that motor is correct, and confirm that it’s blinking. Also, make sure the motor is not connected to a CANivore.

And is it giving you the same error for other motors?

posts.name: Jackson
posts.cooked: The motor is blinking orange, however we do have it connected to a CANivore. Is there a reason we can’t connect it to a CANivore?

posts.name: Mohammed
posts.cooked:
Well that seems to be the reason, when creating a TalonFX object that is connected to a CANivore you also have to set the name of the CANivore that its connected to;

You can use Phoenix Tuner X to check/edit the CANivore name (‘CANivores’ tab).
